    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Building gRPC using `ExternalProject_Add` should now be possible without actually needing any submodules.\r\nIn https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/14822, I am adding a cmake \"superbuild\" example that demonstrates that (and there's a distribtest that verifies it works). The only difference between the superbuild example and what you are suggesting is the example takes the sources from locally-checked out working copy (but that's mostly for our convenience and making it more maintainable), but it should work equally well when URL, URL_HASH (or GIT_REPO and GIT_TAG) are being specified."
